postcontent: Anybody looking for a graded Fox 20ga. sure knows how scarce they are getting. We at Vintage Firearms buy every sound, viable one we can find for our customers. This gun, sn200517 built in 1915, was purchased as a gun to clean up and restore. We only buy guns for this purpose that are sound and will make a near perfect restoration...or why bother, right? I have decided to list this gun as it is because we are backlogged in our work and there are guys out there just looking for a good shooter at a good price, and that is what this gun is. One of about 2400 total A Grade Fox 20 gauge guns made, and produced during the time when some of the best Fox guns were made, it has a good amount of honest wear on it. Also a bit unusual is that it was ordered for heavier loads, with its 28" #2 weight barrels and weighing 6 1/2lbs. It is still light for a 20ga. but has F/F chokes and a minimum barrel wall thickness of 36 thou, so if it comes to late season pheasants or any heavier load, this is the gun. We can alter the chokes for you if requested, and in fact if you like the gun, we can do any part of the restoration you may desire. Once the gun belongs to a customer and needs attention, we go right to work on it, so any work requested will be done within a few months. The gun is ready to hunt just as she sits, and you can pretty her up a little at a time as the budget allows. A great Fox at an affordable price, with great stock dimensions for modern shooters.

title: For Sale:  DTA SRS Gen I chassis OD Green
postcontent:
I have available for purchase a DTA SRS Gen I chassis with two conversion kits. Here's the breakdown:

-DTA SRS Gen I chassis
-OD Green
-monopod

-.308 kit:

-22" fluted barrel
-factory brake
-bolt
-1 mag
-Exactly 380rds. 168 and 175 FGMM only

-.338LM kit:

-26" fluted barrel
-factory brake (not shown)
-thread protector
-bolt
-1 mag
-Zero rounds. I am the second owner of this rifle. It was purchased from a friend. I have no reason to doubt him. I have never even installed it.

-EXTRAS:

-custom bolt knobs from a member here. One of each kind he made. Originals included.
-custom butt pad from a member here
-Atlas bipod with QD lever and custom, sharp as fuck, SS feet.
-DTA factory soft case with shooting mat. Mint (except for some cat hair. Sorry)
-Operators Kit

-Some other factoids:

-Rifle was sent back to DTA when I first bought it to have the monopod installed. While it was there, they went through every screw and spring and replaced anything that looked out of spec. The trigger is very nice.

-As some sharp eyed members might notice, I had a small section of the top 1913 rail professionally machined off . When I had my S&B 5-25 mounted in a Spuhr mount, the objective bell touched the rail. It looks fine, like I said it was professionally done by my gunsmiths. The rail is of course, easily replaceable.

-The rifle has a couple of safe marks but is in very good shape. I'd rate it 95%.

I know it's Gen I. You all know it is still heavily supported. And as long as you don't try to install the barrel like you're dropping clothespins into a milk bottle (I may have dated myself), the pin system is fine.

-I actually love this rifle. It was my first high end bolt action as I am relatively new to the hobby. But I just got my first Surgeon Scalpel and I have an EDM .338LM/.408CT, so I really don't need this. I am not a collector, I'm more of a get the one, best gun I can for what I want to do. That said, if I never sell it, no big deal. It's that nice.

-TERMS:

-NO TRADES at this time please
-MUST go from me to your FFL . NO exceptions.
-I will NOT separate anything at this time, especially the little goodies I know some of you are eyeing. ;)
-If for whatever reason you purchase the rifle and are not satisfied as to the stated condition, just return it and I will refund you all of your purchase price plus your return shipping and transfer fees. I know that's still a PITA but life is too short to get upset over metal and polymer. Fair as I can make it.
-I ship UPS Ground with tracking number to your FFL. Insurance and/or upgraded shipping is extra.
-I do not mind shipping all of the accessories directly to you separately. Some times, goodies get "lost" at gunshops. Like a black hole.

PRICE IS $4250.00 firm. Payment method is certified funds in the form of bank check.

title: For Sale/Trade:  PPS-43C
postcontent:
SOLD
This is an original Polish PPS-43C in a semi-auto version in the 9mm caliber. It is considered a pistol due to overall length and the 10 inch barrel. The PPS-43C is sometimes referred to as the best SMG of World War II. After WWII, it was widely exported to pro-Soviet regimes around the world, and widely copied.  This historical firearm has been re-designed to shoot from a closed bolt position.  The safety is located at the front of the trigger guard.  The receiver and barrel shroud are made from stamped steel.  The rear sight is an L-shaped flip type and is marked for 100 and 200 meters, the front sight is a fixed blade type.  The barrel is equipped with a simple muzzle brake.  This firearm is an ATF approved pistol.  The stock has no function and is permanently fixed in its folded position. 
It comes with 4-35 rd mags, a sling, case, and a Zombie Stryke Green Laser from NcStar. It is super easy to clean. It come apart in three pieces only.
I have shot aluminum, brass and steel ammo. It all cycles fine. This is fun weapon to shoot, it attracts a lot of attention at the range and is very accurate. The laser helps get you on target when shooting from the hip. I am not trying to make any money I'm just trying to recoup the money I have in it. If you are interested in this weapon give me a shout. 

Contact James,

title: For Trade:  Romanian M44 Carbine
postcontent: I am looking to part with my Romanian M44. The condition of the gun is good for it's age and history with Romanian firearms production. This is a rare M44 that has all matching numbers as most Romanian M44 carbines rarely had matching numbers. Bore is excellent and the bluing has held up great. The stock needs refinished. It's common for these stocks to show more damage than others due to the quick production and quality of the wood. Only ~70,000 of these guns were made so this is definitely a great collector's piece and a great shooter. I will send pictures via email if requested. Thanks
